hopobject.body: Insufficient funds can methylprednisolone cause muscle aches So what components will make up this high street of the future? “It’s about getting the mix right,” Boor explains. “What we don’t want is for the whole place to be seen as only for students, or only for families, or only for people working in the City. We want it to reflect the diversity that is around it and be a far cry from the old 'build and they will come’ attitudes of the past. To be successful, it is going to have to work for the world in which it finds itself – which means it has to look like Southwark. There are 120 languages spoken within a half-mile radius of this development, and a vibrant Latin American community in particular. There’s no point, then, in us trying to create something that looks like a Middle England Little Tweedletown.”
